<i>to show how far we've come,</i>

01:02.711 --> 01:07.113
<i>to acknowledge momentous</i>
<i>moments in our lives.</i>

01:07.115 --> 01:11.517
♪ I'm doin' all right,
gettin' good grades ♪

01:11.519 --> 01:13.353
♪ my future's so bright ♪

01:13.355 --> 01:15.955
♪ I gotta wear shades ♪

01:15.957 --> 01:17.624
♪ I gotta wear shades ♪

01:17.626 --> 01:19.392
<i>For us,</i>
<i>our high school graduation</i>

01:19.394 --> 01:21.494
<i>definitely fits the bill.</i>

01:21.496 --> 01:22.895
- I can't believe we did it!
- Really?

01:22.897 --> 01:24.297
I kinda can't believe <i>I</i> did it.

01:24.299 --> 01:25.531
Pretty sure you were a given.

01:25.533 --> 01:27.567
Oh, it's so weird to think
in just a few months,

01:27.569 --> 01:29.335
we'll all be scattered
across the globe.

01:29.337 --> 01:31.003
And you, my friend,
leave in a week.

01:31.005 --> 01:32.438
I know, but just for the city.

01:32.440 --> 01:33.940
With a job and a paycheck,

01:33.942 --> 01:35.508
living in
your hot boyfriend's loft.

01:35.510 --> 01:37.543
Only for a few weeks until
I find my own place to live.

01:37.545 --> 01:39.912
- Either way, totally cool.
- Well, tell that to my dad.

01:39.914 --> 01:41.948
- He hasn't dropped the silent treatment?
- Nope.

01:41.950 --> 01:43.149
Who would've guessed
<i>your</i> dad would be

01:43.151 --> 01:44.217
the understanding one?

01:44.219 --> 01:45.518
I am as surprised as anyone.

01:45.520 --> 01:47.286
Who knew he would
take the news so well

01:47.288 --> 01:48.254
that I'm going to Pratt?

01:48.256 --> 01:49.822
Maybe our dads switched brains.

01:49.824 --> 01:51.724
I'm just excited
you'll be in the city with me.

01:51.726 --> 01:52.925
Stop making me jealous.

01:52.927 --> 01:55.227
Oh, please, you're gonna be
20 minutes away

01:55.229 --> 01:56.829
from your macho military man.

01:56.831 --> 01:59.031
While I'll be hours and hours
away from everyone

01:59.033 --> 02:01.100
slaving away
at the most prestigious college

02:01.102 --> 02:02.802
in the country
all by my lonesome.

02:02.804 --> 02:04.470
Oy, vey.
Let the pity party begin.

02:04.472 --> 02:05.971
Hi, Mr. London!

02:05.973 --> 02:07.306
Hey, kids.

02:07.308 --> 02:09.108
So, Mouse, you're needed
for pictures with the faculty.

02:09.110 --> 02:10.175
Are you ready?

02:10.178 --> 02:11.644
Yes, I'm ready for my moment.

02:11.646 --> 02:12.812
West's moment as well.

02:12.814 --> 02:14.013
As co-valedictorians,

02:14.015 --> 02:15.548
you'll both be
in the annual picture.

02:15.550 --> 02:18.183
Right. Of course.
I'll be right there.

02:18.185 --> 02:19.852
Hey, what are the odds
that you guys would

02:19.854 --> 02:22.688
get the same G.P.A.
down to the decimal point?

02:22.690 --> 02:24.657
3%. Ugh.

02:24.659 --> 02:26.025
Be back soon.

02:26.027 --> 02:27.760
I'm so proud of you!
Hi!

02:27.762 --> 02:30.295
(Laughs) And you
looked gorgeous up there.

02:30.297 --> 02:31.015
Thanks!

02:31.135 --> 02:32.936
I am one of the few people that can
pull off maroon and gold.

02:33.056 --> 02:33.900
Oh, oh!

02:34.020 --> 02:36.235
That's so funny, babe.
Isn't she the greatest?

02:36.237 --> 02:37.803
- She is.
- The best.

02:37.805 --> 02:39.271
I heard someone say
“The best.”

02:39.273 --> 02:40.439
are you talking about me?

02:40.441 --> 02:42.141
No, actually, we were
talking about me.

02:42.143 --> 02:43.642
Whoa, look at you
and your newfound

02:43.644 --> 02:44.968
sense of confidence. I like
this new Maggie.

02:45.088 --> 02:45.960
Me, too.

02:46.080 --> 02:47.980
- Did we just agree on something?
- Yeah.

02:47.982 --> 02:50.349
But don't worry.
We won't tell anyone.

02:50.351 --> 02:51.884
(Camera shutter clicking) <i> While
it was warm between some,</i>

02:51.886 --> 02:54.786
<i>it was definitely cooler</i>
<i>among others.</i>

02:54.788 --> 02:56.722
Okay, so I think
we have that one.

02:56.724 --> 02:58.290
Great.
Glad that's over.

02:58.292 --> 03:00.692
- I mean, glad you got the photo.
- Yeah, same.

03:00.694 --> 03:02.194
Well, congratulations, you two.

03:02.196 --> 03:03.195
As you both know,

03:03.197 --> 03:05.330
the valedictorian's awarded
a gift...

03:05.332 --> 03:07.366
In your case,
co-valedictorians.

03:07.368 --> 03:09.601
Yes, I am very excited.

03:09.603 --> 03:11.670
We will reach out to you
when your gift arrives.

03:11.672 --> 03:13.138
Terrific. Can't wait.

03:16.042 --> 03:19.044
So, congratulations.

03:19.046 --> 03:21.880
To you, too.

03:21.882 --> 03:23.615
I heard you're going
to Princeton.

03:23.617 --> 03:26.051
Yeah. I have a shot
to play basketball there.

03:26.053 --> 03:27.919
That's great.

03:31.390 --> 03:33.625
Well, it was... good
to see you.

03:33.627 --> 03:34.793
Definitely.

03:34.795 --> 03:36.528
Good luck at school.

03:36.530 --> 03:38.096
You, too.

03:41.233 --> 03:43.468
Well, that was...

03:43.470 --> 03:44.836
(Tom) Awkward.

03:44.838 --> 03:47.439
You winning the Dr. Daniel Banes
Book Scholarship Award,

03:47.441 --> 03:49.941
since you won't be needing
books this year.

03:49.943 --> 03:51.976
- You're not taking this?
- No, you can have it.

03:51.978 --> 03:53.745
Since you won't be
going to college.

03:53.747 --> 03:55.780
Yeah, yeah. We all know
you're disappointed.

03:55.782 --> 03:58.183
But can you just lay off today?
She just graduated.

03:58.185 --> 03:59.450
Thank you.

03:59.452 --> 04:01.085
Although, are you just
being nice to me

04:01.087 --> 04:02.487
because you wanna
move into my room?

04:02.489 --> 04:04.956
That and you looked so hideous
in that cap and gown,

04:04.958 --> 04:07.258
I didn't want the day
to get any worse for you.

04:07.260 --> 04:08.493
Aw, that was sweet of you.

04:08.495 --> 04:10.161
I thought she looked great
in that cap and gown...

04:10.163 --> 04:11.496
So much so that I'd like
to see her in another one

04:11.498 --> 04:12.597
in four years.

04:12.599 --> 04:14.732
It is only June.

04:14.734 --> 04:16.733
Maybe you can still
get your spot at N.Y.U.?

04:16.736 --> 04:18.903
Dad, she is not
going to change her mind.

04:18.904 --> 04:20.838
I took the job
at “Interview.”

04:20.839 --> 04:21.939
I know I'm on my own.

04:21.940 --> 04:23.741
But hopefully,
you can believe in me

04:23.743 --> 04:25.376
and the decisions I've made.

04:25.378 --> 04:28.146
I can't.

04:28.148 --> 04:31.816
Because I truly feel that
you are ruining your future,

04:31.818 --> 04:36.053
and I will not condone that.

04:41.493 --> 04:43.327
Don't worry.

04:43.329 --> 04:45.596
He can't stay mad
at you forever.

04:45.598 --> 04:46.797
You're his favorite.

04:46.799 --> 04:50.701
His favorite daughter to be mad at.
(Chuckles)

04:50.703 --> 04:53.304
Will you at least be
nice to him when I'm gone?

04:53.306 --> 04:55.172
I'll try, but I can't promise.

04:55.174 --> 04:57.942
I'm still me, after all.

05:03.281 --> 05:07.451
<i>It was time</i>
<i>to put away childish things...</i>

05:09.521 --> 05:13.224
<i>and become a working girl.</i>

05:13.226 --> 05:15.492
Thank you.

05:15.494 --> 05:16.894
You ready for the big day?

05:16.896 --> 05:18.228
Um, I think so.

05:18.230 --> 05:19.396
I'm trying to read up
on everything

05:19.398 --> 05:21.699
so I have ideas to pitch
when I get in.

05:21.701 --> 05:25.636
Ah, there's an article
in here about Larissa.

05:25.638 --> 05:26.837
What about?

05:26.839 --> 05:28.906
They are calling her
a modern day Medici,

05:28.908 --> 05:32.476
a benefactor to the burgeoning
art scene in the city.

05:32.478 --> 05:33.444
Oh, get this.

05:33.446 --> 05:35.212
“With Harlan's money
and my taste,

05:35.214 --> 05:37.447
we're going to take
the art world by storm”"

05:37.449 --> 05:39.883
(chuckles) I can't believe
that I work for someone

05:39.885 --> 05:41.585
who has articles
written about her

05:41.587 --> 05:44.354
in the “Arts and Leisure”
section of the paper of record.

05:44.356 --> 05:45.722
That can only be good for you,

05:45.724 --> 05:47.057
having your wagon
hitched to hers.

05:47.059 --> 05:48.258
I mean, look at us.

05:48.260 --> 05:49.793
We're making it big
in this crazy city.

05:49.795 --> 05:52.896
Well, my stuff's more
in California,

05:52.898 --> 05:55.799
and I may need to think
about being there more.

05:55.801 --> 05:58.001
Yeah, of course.
I mean, I figured as much.

05:58.003 --> 06:00.904
Maybe I can pitch story ideas
so I have to head out there

06:00.906 --> 06:02.072
for a few days.

06:02.074 --> 06:04.007
And then we can take
our trips together.

06:04.009 --> 06:05.776
Sure. Yeah.

06:05.778 --> 06:06.943
(Mug thuds) Well, I gotta go.

06:06.945 --> 06:08.812
I don't wanna be late
on my first day.

06:08.814 --> 06:11.681
Have so much fun, Bradshaw.

06:11.683 --> 06:13.850
I will do my best, Kydd.

